---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

// Copy adapted from the action-plan draft (Appendix A), July 2026.
// Huawei is named with permission on all three levels: naming them as a
// client, describing the nature of the work, and citing the campaign's
// reach. EP is running the final wording past them before this ships.
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Partners"
  lang="en"
  description="Partnership, speaking and advisory work with Esa-Pekka Mattila, T54 wheelchair racer, through LA 2028. What a partnership involves and what a season costs."
>
  <section class="partners-hero">
    <div class="wrap">
      <p class="kicker">Partners</p>
      <h1>Partnership,<br />speaking,<br />advisory<span class="accent-text">.</span></h1>
      <p class="lead">
        I am open to partners through LA 2028. This page sets out what
        that means in practice and what it costs, because leaving that
        vague wastes everyone's time.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="narrative" id="partnership">
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="sec-head reveal"><span class="idx mono">01</span><h2>Partnership</h2></div>
      <div class="prose reveal">
        <p>
          A season at world level costs around €20,000 before living
          costs: racing chairs, camps, flights, physiotherapy, entries,
          equipment that wears out and gets replaced. The competitive
          plan runs to the World Championships in Tashkent in June 2027
          and Los Angeles in 2028, and ends there.
        </p>
        <p>
          My own channels are small and I won't pretend otherwise. What
          I bring is the material: twenty years at world level, a
          governance career running alongside it, and a track record of
          saying true things on camera. What a partner brings is
          distribution. When Huawei filmed the work we did together on
          wearable technology, the film reached eight million views — on
          their channels, not mine. That division of labour is the
          model, and it has been tested once already.
        </p>
        <p>
          Terms are defined case by case. I am looking for a small
          number of partners, not a shirt full of logos.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="narrative" id="speaking">
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="sec-head reveal"><span class="idx mono">02</span><h2>Speaking</h2></div>
      <div class="prose reveal">
        <p>
          Keynotes, panels and workshops, in Finnish and English. Topics
          I actually know something about: decision-making under
          constraint, athlete representation when it is more than a
          formality, disability inclusion past the tokenism stage, and
          the systems around elite sport.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="narrative" id="advisory">
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="sec-head reveal"><span class="idx mono">03</span><h2>Advisory</h2></div>
      <div class="prose reveal">
        <p>
          Advisory work in wheelchair and assistive technology — with
          Huawei, taking a product feature from athlete feedback to
          shipped release — and on accessibility and governance
          questions where lived experience, board experience and
          business-law training point at the same problem. From a
          sparring session to a defined project.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="partners-cta">
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="rule-accent"></div>
      <p class="cta-line">Start a conversation.</p>
      <a href="mailto:ep@esapekkamattila.com" class="cta-mail">ep@esapekkamattila.com</a>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .partners-hero {
    padding-top: clamp(140px, 20vh, 200px);
    padding-bottom: var(--space-5);
  }
  .partners-hero h1 {
    margin-top: var(--space-2);
  }
  .accent-text {
    color: var(--accent);
  }
  .partners-hero .lead {
    margin-top: var(--space-4);
    font-size: var(--text-lead);
    line-height: 1.3;
    font-weight: 500;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    max-width: 32rem;
  }

  .narrative {
    border-top: 1px solid var(--rule);
    /* Clears the fixed nav when arriving via /partners#speaking */
    scroll-margin-top: 90px;
  }
  .narrative .prose p {
    font-size: clamp(1.0625rem, 1.5vw, 1.1875rem);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-2);
    max-width: 44rem;
  }
  .narrative .prose p:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }
  .sec-head {
    display: flex;
    align-items: baseline;
    gap: 16px;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-3);
  }
  .sec-head .idx {
    color: var(--accent);
    font-size: 0.75rem;
  }

  .partners-cta {
    border-top: 1px solid var(--rule);
  }
  .cta-line {
    margin-top: var(--space-3);
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: var(--text-h2);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    line-height: var(--line-tight);
  }
  .cta-mail {
    display: inline-block;
    margin-top: var(--space-2);
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
  }
</style>
